    "description": "Visual Processing Japan Co., Ltd. engages in the development of digital asset management (DAM) solutions in Japan. The company offers DAM solution to support the business activities of companies by providing assistance on media content production, management and distribution. It provides CIERTO that integrates digital asset management and product information management to support the production of content across various platforms, such as e-commerce sites, websites, videos, social media, catalogs, and brochures; APROOOVE WM, a project management solution for content production such as catalogs, brochures, videos, and websites; and WoodWing Studio, an online editing and distribution system that enables online editing of media consisting of magazines, newspapers, and documents. The company serves distribution and retail, manufacturing, service, printing, housing and real estate, media and publishing, pharmaceutical and chemical, finance and insurance, and travelling and sightseeing industries. The company was incorporated in 1994 and is headquartered in Shibuya, Japan."
